    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "Based on the researcher's remarks, some important abilities and features of ANN applied to fuel consumption prediction include the following: (1) ANNs are able to learn, associate, and be error tolerant providing better prediction results in comparison to regression models (Rahimi-Ajdadi, Abbaspour-Gilandeh 2011); (2) can handle large and complex systems with many interrelated parameters; Kara Togun, Baysec 2010); (3) possess powerful modelling capability to identify complex relationships from input-output data and generalize a wide range of experimental conditions; (4) the use of ANN models is quicker, more convenient and cost-effective than fully experimental studies; (5) can contain multiple input variables to predict multiple output variables; (6) the ANN approach represents fast calculation methodology that does not require complex mathematical equations to explain a non-linear and multi-dimensional system (Özener et al. 2013 ); (7) the massive volume and complexity of field dataset make this data-driven approach is more suitable in comparison to other modelling methods, particularly regression-based models which's development may be a vary laborious, if not unfeasible, task"
    },
